This paper is about multi-label classification for aerial images, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel network architecture that incorporates label relations, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which is a popular research area in computer vision and natural language processing (cs.IR). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on two datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
